## Testing plan

Gates (always all three): `build`, `unit-tests`, `constructor-unit-tests`.

- `constructor-unit-tests` gate runs the new `OpticalConstructor.Tests` files; must pass and increase the count over the prior slice's baseline.
- AC-J6 (`EnvironmentRoundTripTests.fs`): `EnvironmentSettings` serializes to JSON, validates against `optical-constructor-environment.schema.json`, round-trips (favorites board, recent files, last folder, panel layout, preferences preserved); a deliberately invalid file falls back to built-in defaults without migration; never `.binz`.
- AC-J7: editing a default-unit or wavelength-range preference affects only display/boundary formatting and leaves stored `double<meter>` values byte-identical; solver defaults are the engine's `SolverParameters` (`Solvers.fs:15`), no parallel solver-config record.
- AC-J8: theme + panel layout round-trip through `EnvironmentSettings` JSON; confirm `OpticalConstructor.Ui.fsproj` contains no reference to `C:\GitHub\Avalonia.FuncUI.Clone\` and the linking mechanism is unresolved (the `build` gate compiles `AppShell` against the public MIT FuncUI DSL).
- AC-J9 (`ValidationTests.fs`): non-positive finite thickness (`Thickness.Thickness d`, `d <= 0.0<meter>`), repeat count < 1, and empty/invalid wavelength range each return `Result.Error` without throwing or coercing; valid inputs return `Ok`.
- `build` gate green at Release/x64; `unit-tests` gate (BerremanTests) stays green (not touched here).

## Risks

- **Medium.** Two load-bearing disciplines: (1) `EnvironmentSettings` must persist as schema-validated JSON reusing the slice-003 shared `JsonSerializerOptions` — never `.binz`, never a second JSON stack — with fall-back-to-defaults (not migration) on validation failure; (2) `AppShell` must compile against the public MIT FuncUI DSL while keeping the audit-gated clone unreferenced and its linking mechanism unresolved (the spec-0110-class failure mode). Mitigation: prove the round-trip and the defaults-fallback by test; grep the UI fsproj for any clone path before exit; keep `Validation` validators pure (`Result`, no exceptions, no unit conversion).

## Hand-off

The persistent environment exists: `EnvironmentSettings`/`Preferences` (`UserEnvironment.fs`) with the favorites board, recent files, panel layout, theme, and preferences round-tripping through schema-validated JSON; the `AppShell` dockable shell authored against the FuncUI DSL surface (clone unreferenced, linking unresolved); and the J.9 `Validation` module that slice 014's J.2 already calls. AC-J6/AC-J7/AC-J8/AC-J9 tests green. Slice 016 (LAST) adds the `JobRunner` (whose active job appears in this slice's `AppShell` shared status area), the `Help` gallery, and the `SystemView3D` viewport. Emit the state-of-the-world file with all required ATX headings (`Where we are`, `What's working`, `Tests`, `Architecture`, `Deferred`, `Gotchas`, `Changelog`) and a fenced `gates:` YAML baseline block carrying the updated `constructor-unit-tests` count so the next slice's `count_at_least` gate has a baseline.
